    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-16T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-16T08:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <head>380. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Delegation at the Foreign Ministers
                        Meetings</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d380fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 396.1–<gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>/11–1655. Confidential. The
                        meeting took place at 10:30 a.m. on November 16.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-11-16T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1955—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 323. At tripartite Ministerial meeting
                    November 16 it agreed to table in conference proposed statement to be made by
                    four Foreign Ministers (text in immediately following cable<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d380fn2">
                        <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 324 from Geneva, November 16, not
                        printed. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>) For text of the statement on
                        disarmament, see <hi rend="italic">Foreign Ministers Meeting</hi>, p. 227,
                        or <hi rend="italic">Cmd</hi>. 9633, p. 134.</note>).</p>
                <p>Secretary stated his assumption that in terms of guidance to US, UK and French
                    representatives on UN Disarmament Subcommittee this paper would not supersede
                    previous tripartite paper tabled at conference at 10th session November
                        10th<note n="3" xml:id="d380fn3">For text of this proposal, see <hi
                            rend="italic">Foreign Ministers Meeting</hi>, pp. 199–201, or <hi
                            rend="italic">Cmd</hi>. 9633, pp. 132–133.</note> which would serve as
                    guidance to our UN representatives. <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Macmillan</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_PA1">Pinay</persName> fully
                    concurred saying present paper was tactical move and did not supersede or
                    replace original paper.</p>
            </div>
